HEADWORD: Countergage
<hw>Coun"ter*gage`</hw> <pr>(-g⟦amac⟧j`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Carp.)</fld> <def>An adjustable gauge, with double points for
transferring measurements from one timber to another, as the breadth of
a mortise to the place where the tenon is to be made.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

